My favorite thing to make for parties: Christmas Tree Cheese Ball with various olives, sun dried tomatoes and sprigs of rosemary for decorations, topped with a gold yellow pepper star!
.
Serve it with bagel slices for breakfast OR serve with crackers for a festive appetizer. And, my favorite part is, it keeps FOREVER and goes great with bagels for breakfast or can be used to make pinwheels! Steve always hopes people don't eat it all. ha! :) 
.
I made it with low-fat @phillycreamchs cream cheese and fresh ingredients like chives, red peppers and some diced dill pickles, garlic powder and onion powder to add some zip!
.
It's always a hit and relatively easy to make (and FUN). You could do this with pretty much any cheese ball recipe. It's beautiful and delicious!
.
.
.
.
.

This is the month we often start thinking of our failures as we fly through the food-centered holiday season - Halloween candy, pumpkin pie, christmas cookies, Eggnog...it seems almost impossible not to fail. 
.
Then we look at the new year and, again, it's hard to think of our New Year Goals without thinking of our last year's failures.
.
Failure is required for success. You can't have great success without it. 
.
But, failure means you tried. You set the bar, but you didn't reach it. However, what if you didn't set the bar at all? What if you didn’t have a goal, join the gym, try a diet, etc? Then where would you be? I bet you are better off trying and failing than not trying at all. 
.
Instead of focusing on your failures, celebrate your attempts. You were BRAVE. You TRIED! And you should continue to try until the day you die - to be better, healthier, wiser, more experienced, etc. Don't let past failures prevent you from setting new goals and trying once again. XOXO
.
.
.
.
#motivation #pfitblog #failure #tryagain #justdoit #fitnessmotivation #newyear #resolutions

Isn't it SO EASY to recognize areas of weakness in other people that aren't an issue for you? We often say "I would NEVER do that" yet we would do something else that others are thinking "I would never do THAT".
.
As @stevepfiester says, "keep your eyes on your own paper". Of course he says that in the gym when we are looking at how much stronger someone else is or how many more reps another client is doing compared to you, but we need to keep our eyes on our own paper when it comes to people's weaknesses too.
.
Scripture says love COVERS sin. Literally. It doesn't just cover it like "I got ya covered", it covers it up. People who love others don't expose weaknesses, the cover them with compliments on their strengths and the benefit of doubt. It does us no good to put people down or expose others weaknesses. But, it does us SO GOOD to be the one who LIFT OTHERS up. It might be just what that person needs - someone to believe in them when no one else does.
.
LESS CRITICAL IN 2023
.
Matt 6:1-3
.
.
.
.

MY #1 TIP TO CRUSH GOALS
🎯 Describe the best version of yourself in GREAT detail and write it down.
.
What does that person look like?
.
What does he/she do every day?
.
What are his/her habits?
.
What is his/her attitude?
.
Describe his/her personality.
.
How does he/she feel?
.
What commitments does he/she make (and keep)?
.
Where will that person be in 1, 5, 10… years?
.
THINK ABOUT IT:
How can you become the best version of yourself if you don’t even know what that person looks like? That’s like going on a road trip and expecting to get to a destination without looking at a map or getting an address.
.
We need constant reminders of who we WANT to be. We know what our first wants (eat, drink, sleep, get more, do less, etc) but we have to remind ourselves daily what we REALLY want. Scripture helps me with that but it is also good to picture what that person will look like if I let God do a work in me and I also do my part.
.
Who’s willing to commit to me RIGHT NOW to describing the best version of yourself today. Write it down. Keep it out to read and reread. If so, this is YOUR YEAR!
.
FOLLOW @beautyandthebeachradio and look for our 2 goal crusher shows for more tips! 
.
.
.

I’ve been asking myself this question a lot lately - fighting off temptations like swapping a mosquitos with a fly swatter! It’s SO MUCH EASIER to say “no” to what you want now (food, laziness, etc) when you compare it to what you want MOST.
.
You can’t just ask yourself this once or twice a week. You have to ask yourself this continually thorough the day - when you are tempted to…waste time scrolling social media, shop Amazon for meaningless junk, skip a workout, sleep in, eat crap, procrastinate in the things that really need to be done, etc. It’s a question that demands an answer. And, honestly, there might be times you want something now more than what you thought you want most because you don’t really want “that” thing that bad.
.
This has helped me SO MUCH fight temptations while I’m dieting and thought I’d share it with my instagram friends. :)
.
.
.
.
.
.

I came across this Photo Booth strip of me with my mom - probably in the Tallahassee Mall in the mid to late 70s. I was missing a tooth and was about as dorky and awkward as I could get. 
.
And my mom, like always, radiated beauty and love - and somehow made me feel pretty and capable …like I could do anything.
.
That’s a special super power - to make that toothless long legged gawky girl feel as if she could do and be anything.
.
Maybe it’s because I fed off of her beauty and coolness. Maybe just being with her made me feel cool by association. Or maybe she just constantly pointed out all my strengths instead of all my flaws. She showed me my potential daily and believed in me even when I didn’t. I remember her telling me I was a leader when I was probably 8 years old. I didn’t see it. I was “just a kid”.
.
I’m so thankful for her love, mentorship and friendship. I actually still feel empowered when I’m with her. Together, we can do anything. ❤️
.
How do we make people feel when they are around us? Do we leave them better or worse? Stronger or weaker? Inspired or hopeless?
.
We all have the power to  impact people in our lives everywhere we go - from our own family to the grocery store clerk. I wonder what they’d say about us after we walk away….
.
.
.
.
#throwbackthursday #throwback #throwbackthursdays #70skid #70s #motherdaughter #love #mentor #inspired

Hard work, but fun work! 
We are Riptide! 

If you had to request one song to dance to, what would it be?

How amazing is it I get to sing and play with my mom - and even more amazing, that they are healthy and fit enough to work a long full day loading and unloading band equipment, enduring tedious sound checks with all the newest technology, playing their heart out and keeping late nights with us with a smile on their faces. It’s hard to believe they’ve been at this for over 50 years! And they still got it!
.
She started off at Winewood Country club with her first professional solo gig while my dad played drums at @killearncc  in Tallahassee, Florida. Then she joined Shamrock at Killearn and they were the house band there for the first 13 years of my life. Every single Friday and Saturday - and every holiday.
.
They pkayed for the governor (Bob Graham back then I believe) and did other special events around town. They played at the Brien Derby - anyone remember that place? Lol
.
Now we play for country clubs in #verobeach (this photo was taken last night at @grandharborclub country club). 
.
FUN FACT: Back then, they played the radio in the mall. Mom and dad did a lot of jingles for commercials - like Duncan Donuts, Waterbed Delight and few others I can’t remember… Investor’s realty? And a bank. There were several. Anyway, it was always fun to go shopping and hear my parents on the radio. I was always so proud of them - but NEVER did I think I’d do this with them.
.
Just waking up feeling an enormous amount of gratitude for them and for investing in me, teaching me to play and sing, and giving me opportunities to do it together.
.
.
.
.
.
.

What a GREAT experience working with @irchabitat ! Not only have I learned new skills, like putting up siding and laying floors, I get to play with power tools (YAY!) and work with such great people! We work hard but we have fun. None of us have to be there. It’s a choice we gladly make - and the atmosphere on the build site is so joyful because of it.

Each morning starts with a meet up and prayer. You get to meet new people every time, and you get to be a part of something bigger than yourself. I’m so thankful for all the people who have a vision, like Habitat, and for the sacrifices everyone makes, both physically and financially, to make great things happen.

The key to joy is getting your mind off ourselves (which is quiet difficult). It’s soooo hard to not be selfish. The only way to combat it is to purposefully think of others more - which doesn’t come naturally for me at all. 

I was an only kid. I didn’t have to think about anyone else. I just took care of myself, entertained myself, and was quite content being by myself. But that’s not how God wants me to live. 

It’s funny how the more we focus on ourselves, and seek things to make us happy, the more unhappy we become. 

We live in a works today where everyone wants to be important and “liked” on social media. What is really powerful is being a blessing. ❤️ 

I still have a long ways to go but I look forward to growing in this area, serving more, loving more and giving more.

“Carry each other’s burdens, and in this way you will fulfill the law of Christ.” - Galatians 6:2

Mondays are often a big weigh-in day at our gym - and not everyone has a good one. In fact, I am one of those people who didn't have a good one. I was sooooo disappointed. After cleaning up my diet, training hard and not cheating, I expected better - MUCH better. Of course, this ain't my first rodeo and I know it WILL come off eventually, butI wanted it off YESTERDAY lol. duh 😂
. 
So, I walked away from the InBody discouraged, sad...and then MAD. Not made enough to quit, but even MADDER! Mad enough to take everything up a notch and force my body into submission!
.
If eating clean isn't cutting it, then I will log all my food and track every calorie and macro. If training isn't cutting it, I will train harder and more often. If it takes longer, I will keep going until I get the results I want.
.
I refuse to let a little failure turn into a LOT of failure by being tempted to give up or slack out of self pity. Nope! I'm just going to dig my heels in even harder!
.
We have a choice. When we get knocked down, we can stay down - or get back up and ready to fight. Which one will you choose today?
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

Make sure you train your dog like you would a human:
✅Hydrate properly 
✅Watch for overheating
✅Exercise them with rest
✅Give them shade
✅No when they are “done”
✅Give them time off to heal
✅Feed them quality food and supplements to recover
✅Praise them for achievements
✅And stay consistent
.

Still running the same route 20 years later…now in my 50s - determined to fight aging and stay healthy.

I’m not fast. I don’t even really “love it” but I love what it does for me.

I don’t run to train for races.
I don’t run for fat loss.
I don’t run because I want to. lol

I run for my mental, spiritual and physical health. I run to get away from notifications, work and unhealthy distractions.

I turn on Bible teaching and hit the pavement expecting to learn, grow, enjoy nature and improve.

I return to my house stronger than I left. THAT’s why I run.

But, I don’t “just run”. I have to hit the gym too. Our body needs strength training. Again, I don’t do it because I love it. I do it because my body does. I pretty much am a lazy fart. lol. But, time after time, my body reminds me how important it is. I feel my best when I do what is best for me. It’s not always easy. In fact, most of the time it sucks lol until it’s done. But the rest of the day ROCKS and THAT’s why I keep doing it over and over and over.

I’m not looking to do something NEE in 2024, I’m looking to stay committed to what I started years ago despite life, struggles, age, etc.

#running #run #runner #justdoit #fitnessmotivation #fitness #goals #healthyliving #iam12strong

I HAAAATE posting this. UGH. I just felt like I needed to share my reality. Social media can be so skewed for people who never see you face to face and I wanted to keep things honest as possible.

Earlier this week I posted an old running pic I came across, talking about running the same route for 20 years. I never thought people would think it was a recent pic because my hair was longer then. Everyone was so nice and complimentary but I didn't want to reply to every comment "that's an old pic", and I didn't want people to think I was being dishonest so I thanked everyone and decided to post a recent pic and share my journey with everyone in one post.

Like many of people I talk with, COVID was something that affected me quite a bit. I had FUN being "OFF". We dated, ate, played, got lazy, got comfortable...and, eventually, it showed and I honestly didn't care (at first). 

I always say "what you eat in private will eventually show up in public". Well, that happened to me! I was enjoying being "off" for a change. After years of strict diets and trying to stay lean year round, I embraced the excuse to take time off from caring quite as much.

The first pic was me right before COVID. The middle picture was me earlier this year (GROSS!). That was the pic that made me mad enough to get with the program. ha! The last pic I snapped a few minutes ago. No filters, just me, bad hair 😩 Almost just as gross to me honestly. I hate selfies!!!

I weigh about the same as the running pic but my skin is older lol, I'm not quite as lean and I lost some muscle from my slack workout schedule. But, I'm on my way and I feel like me again.

Many of us milked the new post-COVID "new normal" excuse for long enough. It's time to quit settling for this "new normal" and create our "new best". Normal is lame and we do not have to accept it. We have more control over our lives than we want to admit.

Take back control. 
Turn your setback into your comeback.

There's no excuse for not working to be our very best at any age and in any situation. No excuse at all.

 2024 is the year for no excuses!

MORE THAN MACROS...
I was just chatting with someone this morning, reflecting on my own fitness journey. Several years ago, when I started competing, I was so focused on macro nutrients (protein, carbs, etc), I honestly discounted all the micro nutrients and ingredients. I just knew I what I needed to sculpt my physique - lose fat, build muscle, etc.
As I get older, my health gets more and more important. When I was competing, and appearing to be in the shape of my life, I honestly felt awful. I was in a mental fog, I couldn't focus, lost my drive, quit dreaming and even fell into a little depression - seemingly for no reason.

LABEL LYING
Someone I admire reached out to me and talked to me about the epidemic of label lying (where companies skew the facts, add fillers, hide bad ingredients and just straight up lie) and it really shocked me. I was so trusting. Surely health companies want to create and sell healthy products. Sadly, they want to make money more and most will cut costs and compromise to do it.

My friend challenged me to pay more attention to ingredient, micro-nutrients, get on 100% natural products and try adding more quality supplements to my life just for 30 days. Honestly, even with me understanding what she was saying, I was not into taking a lot of supplements and I was a COMPLETE skeptic - expecting zero change. 

Within a week, my health completely turned around - I CAME TO LIFE! ...and I never looked back. 

I say all of this to hopefully convince you of the importance in investing in your health. Just because you eat enough protein or workout and take vitamins doesn't mean you don't have deficiencies. I was completely whacked when it came to my nutrition and I ate "healthy".

I'll be sharing things I have learned over the years in my 12 STRONG CHALLENGE. Join me if you want some motivation! It's FREE! :) Link in bio.

DAY 1 of the 12 STRONG CHALLENGE!! 

This is a reminder to just show up whether you feel like it or not. Meal prep whether you feel like it or not. Make healthy choices whether you feel like it or not. Stay committed whether you feel like it or not.

IGNORE YOUR EMOTIONS

Success is not determined on how you feel, it is determined on what you do. 

Emotions drive you to do stupid things. Put them aside for the facts. And, the fact is, if you workout and eat right, your life will change. You WILL get healthier and feel better. You don't need to feel some magical motivation inside to do it. 

You can do it afraid.
You can do it tired.
You can do it full of doubt.
You can do it even when you don't want to.
You can even do it mad.
Just do it how you can with what you have.

If you do it, results will come - and the results will start motivating you to keep doing it. 

Then friends will start to notice and they will motivate you to keep doing it.

Then the new you will not want to ever be the old you and your reflection in the mirror will motivate you to keep doing it.

The hardest part is getting started - showing up, even when no part of you feels ready or wants to do any of it.

JUST DO IT.

#IAM12STRONG

IT’S YOU AGAINST YOU!

If you are starting over (again) this year, you have the advantage. You know you better than anyone. You know your weaknesses and strengths. You know what has worked before and what hasn’t. You know what you are up against. It’s YOU.

When I wrote this, I was being tempted to fall into the trap of comparisons and I asked myself “what am I training for”? My answer was: I just wanted to beat the old me. I wanted to be MY best, not THE best. I wanted to ditch the lazy girl who was comfortable being “ok”. I wanted to push myself out of my comfort zone (which I loved by the way lol). 

YOUR OPPONENT

No one is more against your success than YOU - your own weaknesses, struggles, excuses, cravings, desires, emotions and doubts. But, you can combat that. You don’t have to give in to that. As soon as you see that play coming, you can run in the other direction.

There is no athlete who wouldn’t want that kind of advantage - to know their opponents plays so they can beat them.

You have the upper hand. You can beat the old you. You can be ready for whatever she/he throws your way because it’s nothing new. You’ve had years of practice.

You can look at starting over as weakness or you can use it as a strength - going in more experienced than before.

You got this. We got this.

#iam12strong
